<br>
Advantage 1,2,3,4,5,6,7: SLAM! I don't think I really need to say all that much more. <br>
<br>
Advantage 8: Regeneration. It really does help in the early levels. <br>
<br>
Advantage 9: Incredible Strength. If you're encumbered, you have pretty poor gear.. (i.e, fulll large bronze.) Plus, it does help your damage a little.<br>
<br>
Advantage 10: Incredible stamina. You will have many more HP than me at the higher levels.<br>
<br>
Disadvantage 1: Faction: You'll be hurting for this at first in, well, everywhere but Grobb, not even Neriak will be particularly fond of you. <br>
<br>
Disadvantage 2: You're big, and you're uglier than sin. This does get to be a problem in many dungeons.<br>
<br>
Disadvantage 3: Yer dumb as a rock. You'll need a ton of int gear to solo, or pull. <br>
<br>
Eruds: <br>
Advantage one: You'll have better faction than most trolls and ogres, much like a dark elf, I believe. <br>
<br>
Advantage two: You'll have a _really_ high int, and the enormous mana pool that goes with it. <br>
<br>
Advantage three: You'll look fairly cool, and pretty unique.<br>
<br>
Disadvantage 1: You're blind.<br>
<br>
Disadvantage 2: You're weak. Poor strength and stamina lead to some interesting gear considerations, since you have comparatively few HPs, and a low encumbrance without lots of the proper gear. <br>
<br>
Disadvantage 3: You'll need a shield to interrupt spells. While there are a lot of really cool shields out there, (Ashenbone, bladestopper, heck, even Sentry come to mind), be aware that you'll be giving up things like the Deathbringer's rod to interrupt spells. <br>
<br>
Disadvantage 4:Erud's Isle sucks. Get off it. NOW! <br>
<br>
<br>
